<script type="text/javascript">
function togPhase(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + n);
	e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
}
function togAllPhases(display) {
	for (var i = 1; i <= 50; i++) {
		var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + i);
		if (!e) break;
		e.style.display = display;
	}
}
function addHint(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phase');
	for (var i = 0; i < e.childNodes.length; i++) {
		e.childNodes[i].selected = e.childNodes[i].value == n ? 'selected' : '';
	}
	e = document.getElementById('text');
	e.focus();
	e.select();
}
</script>

<div class="mm white">
This quest  is called '<span class="yellow">Music to My Ears!</span>',<br/>
for Adventurers levels <span class="yellow">241</span> to <span class="yellow">241</span>.<br />


<span class="hg"><a href="/npc/255">Lord Vendredi</a> [<a href="/area/51">Sigil</a>] is the master in charge of this quest.</span><br />

Taunted by the whimsical music of bards, Lord Vendredi has always wished<br />
for a talented bard to entertain him in his Audience Chamber.  It would<br />
appear that the current town bard, Garan is a bit flighty and really is not<br />
right for the job.  Lord Vendredi would like for you to journey about Alyria<br />
to seek out a proper bard for his castle.  The retired bard, Izydor may be<br />
able to give you some history on bards to help in your journey.  Remember<br />
that the music forces in Xaventry, New Rigel and Pirate's Cove can help you.<br />
Don't forget to make use of Lowangen's Balloon traveling system as it is<br />
quite marvelous.  Do not delay as Lord Vendredi appears to be quite bored<br />
with the current company he keeps.<br />

<span class="hy">Upon successful completion of this quest you can receive:</span><br />

<span class="hm">*</span>Up to <span class="yellow">90</span> quest points, <span class="yellow">10</span> practice points, <span class="yellow">0</span> experience points,<br/>
&nbsp;<span class="yellow">0</span> build points, <span class="yellow">0</span> piety, and <span class="yellow">8,000</span> gold pieces.<br />


You have <span class="yellow">300</span> minutes remaining to complete this quest.<br />

Music to My Ears! consists of:<br />


	<div class="phase" id="phase1">


		<a class="hints" href="javascript:togPhase(1);">Phase 1</a>: Rescue <a href="/npc/3086">An elven bard</a>. 		
		<div class="phasehints" id="phasehint1" style="display: none;">

<div class="phaseinfomob">in <a href="/area/1">Alyria</a>.</div>


			<div class="phasehint">
				In many forests of Alyria. I find them south of New Rigel.				&mdash;
				Tejon							</div>


			<div class="phasehint">
				Just outside of Lowangan too.				&mdash;
				Kirali							</div>


		</div>
	</div>


	<div class="phase" id="phase2">


		<a class="hints" href="javascript:togPhase(2);">Phase 2</a>: Defeat <a href="/npc/175">The traveling bard</a>. 		
